  "text": "Trait method resolution in rustc lives in `compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/`. Three files are central: (1) **probe.rs** contains `ProbeContext` which assembles candidate trait method implementations via `assemble_inherent_candidates`, `assemble_extension_candidates_for_traits_in_scope`, and related helpers, then selects among them in `pick`/`pick_method`/`pick_core`. (2) **mod.rs** defines `MethodError::Ambiguity(Vec<CandidateSource>)` \u2014 the error variant produced when multiple candidate implementations match \u2014 and `CandidateSource` (enum with `Impl` and `Trait` variants). (3) **suggest.rs** contains `report_method_error` (line 145) which handles reporting ambiguous trait method errors to the user, including the E0034 'multiple applicable items in scope' diagnostic (line 225-226).",
